    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Board
     
    Client
    Represents a single connected game client in the TCP-based server architecture.
    Command
    Base class for all serializable game commands exchanged between the client and the server.
    Command.Status
    Marker interface for representing command execution status.
    CommandAck
    Represents an acknowledgement command sent in response to the reception of another Command.
    CommandRe
    Base class for all response commands returned by the server or client.
    CommandRe.Status
    Enumeration of standard response statuses.
    Echo
     
    Echo.Cmd
     
    Echo.CmdRe
     
    Game
     
    GameServer
    High-level game server coordinating domain-level game logic and handling game-related commands delivered through a lower-level TCPServer.
    GameServerConnector
    High-level networking connector used by the game client to communicate with the remote game server.
    GameState
    Marker interface for all serializable data structures representing the state of various elements in the game.
    GameState.BoardInfo
    Immutable descriptor of global board metadata.
    GameState.BoardSquareInfo
    Information about a single square on the game board.
    GameState.Pack
    Specifies which part of the game state is being updated.
    GameState.PlayerDesc
    Lightweight player descriptor used for board-level views (e.g., showing each player's location on the board).
    GameState.PlayerInfo
    Full information about a single player, suitable for rendering the player's panel or status data.
    GameState.PlayerListInfo
    Contains the list of players participating in the game along with the index of the currently active player.
    GameState.Position
    Represents a column/row position on the game board.
    GetInfo
     
    GetInfo.Cmd
     
    GetInfo.CmdRe
     
    GetInfo.CmdRe.Info
     
    Handshake
     
    Handshake.Cmd
     
    Handshake.CmdRe
     
    Handshake.CmdRe.Status
     
    JoinGame
     
    JoinGame.Cmd
     
    JoinGame.CmdRe
     
    JoinGame.CmdRe.Status
     
    LeaveGame
     
    LeaveGame.Cmd
     
    LeaveGame.CmdRe
     
    LeaveGame.CmdRe.Status
     
    NetworkConnector
    Defines a low-level abstraction for network communication between the game client and the server.
    Player
     
    RequestMove
     
    RequestMove.Cmd
     
    RequestMove.CmdRe
     
    RequestMove.CmdRe.Status
     
    SocketConnector
    Default implementation of NetworkConnector that uses TCP sockets for communication between the client and the game server.
    TCPServer
    Low-level TCP server responsible for accepting socket connections, handling raw client I/O and routing incoming Command objects to a higher-level command executor.
    UpdateState
    Represents a command used to transmit updated game state information from the server to clients.
    UpdateState.Cmd
    Command sent from the server to clients containing updated game state information.
    UpdateState.CmdRe
    Response command acknowledging the receipt and processing of an UpdateState.Cmd.
    UpdateState.CmdRe.Status
    Status of the update state operation.
    UpdateStateFactory
    Factory class for creating UpdateState.Cmd instances.
    UpdateStateFactory.StateSource
    Represents a source of state updates for an UpdateState.Cmd.
    Version
    Auto-generated version class.
